<div>		



<span class="section_title">INNOVATIONS 2007 AWARDS SEEK THE BEST OF THE BEST IN CONSUMER ELECTRONICS DESIGN AND ENGINEERING</span>

	<br><br>
	<span class="subhead">Call for Entries Open August 28 - October 2, 2006</span>

<br><br>		
<strong><i>Arlington, Virginia&nbsp;-&nbsp;8/28/2006</i></strong>
<br><br>
Entries for the prestigious International CES Innovations 2007 Design 

and Engineering Awards will be accepted today through October 2, 2006, announced the Consumer Electronics 

Association (CEA<sup>&#174</sup>). This annual competition honors outstanding design and engineering in cutting-edge 

consumer electronics. The awards are sponsored by CEA, the producer of the International CES, and endorsed by the 

Industrial Designers Society of America (IDSA) - the voice of industrial design, committed to advancing the 

profession through education, information, community and advocacy.  The 2007 International CES, the world's largest 

consumer technology tradeshow, runs January 8-11, 2007 in Las Vegas, Nevada.
<p>
      "Our Innovations program continues to get more popular and more competitive every year," said Karen Chupka, 

senior vice president of conferences and events, CEA.  "The quality of product submissions is also extremely 

impressive and we look forward to receiving the entries for the year's hottest and most innovative products."
<p>
      "We are very pleased to partner with CEA again this year on the Innovations Design and Engineering Awards," 

said IDSA President Ron Kemnitzer. "IDSA's involvement in this program demonstrates the important role industrial 

design plays in all aspects of consumer electronics."
<p>
      For more than 16 years, the Innovations Awards program has given developers and manufacturers an excellent 

opportunity to have their products judged by a preeminent panel of engineers, independent designers and journalists. 

Honored products will be announced at the New York Press Preview on November 8 and showcased at the 2007 

International CES.
<p>
      As the most widely renowned consumer technology awards program, the CES Innovations 2007 Awards recognize the 

best designed and engineered products in the categories of:
<p>
