<p>
      Now in its tenth year, the 2007 Best of Innovations awards are given to the most honored products in each 

category. The Best of Innovations honorees will be announced at the 2007 International CES Unveiled@NewYork on 

November 8, 2006. Honorees also are highlighted and featured in the Innovations Showcase at Innovations Plus in the 

Sands exhibit at the Sands Expo and Convention Center/The Venetian during the International CES. 
<p>
      In addition to housing the prestigious Innovations honorees, Innovations Plus at the Sands will feature 

emerging technology exhibits and events, including hot product TechZones focusing on: Bluetooth, Consumer VoIP, 

IPTV, and Robotics. Innovations Plus will be home to nearly all consumer electronics categories from audio to 

wireless; Anytime Anywhere, Mobile & Personal Broadband, Studio@Home, Digital Living Network Alliance, ExpressCard, 

Flex Tech and The Download.  Additionally, the CES Industry Insiders and CES Unveiled will both be there.
<p>
      Media and analysts will get a sneak peek of this year's Innovations Design and Engineering showcase honorees 

during an enhanced and expanded CES Unveiled:  The Official Press Event of CES.  Guests will enjoy cocktails and 

hors d'oeuvres while viewing tabletop product demonstrations and networking with both Innovations honorees and CES 

exhibitors.  CES Unveiled runs from 4 - 7 p.m. on Saturday January, 6 at the Sands/Venetian.  Only credentialed 

media and analysts will be permitted to attend this exclusive sponsored event   
<p>
	<b>Innovations 2007 Design and Engineering Awards are open to anyone, regardless of CES exhibitor status.  

To submit products for Innovations 2007, review last year's winners or register for the show, log onto <a 

href="http://www.CESweb.org/innovations">www.CESweb.org/innovations</a>.</b>
<p>
<p>
<b>ABOUT CEA:</b><br>
&#160&#160&#160&#160&#160The Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) is the preeminent trade association promoting 

growth in the consumer technology industry through technology policy, events, research, promotion and the fostering 

of business and strategic relationships.  CEA represents more than 2,100 corporate members involved in the design, 

development, manufacturing, distribution and integration of audio, video, mobile electronics, wireless and landline 

communications, information technology, home networking, multimedia and accessory products, as well as related 

services that are sold through consumer channels. Combined, CEA's members account for more than $125 billion in 

annual sales.  CEA's resources are available online at <a href="http://www.CE.org">www.CE.org</a>, the definitive 

source for information about the consumer electronics industry.<br>
&#160&#160&#160&#160&#160CEA also sponsors and manages the International CES - Defining Tomorrow's Technology.  All 

profits from CES are reinvested into industry services, including technical training and education, industry 

promotion, engineering standards development, market research and legislative advocacy.
<p>
<b>About IDSA:</b><br>
&#160&#160&#160&#160&#160The Industrial Designers Society of America is committed to advancing the profession of 

industrial design through education, information, community and advocacy.  The conduit between industrial design and 

education, business, government and the public, IDSA is the knowledge source and voice for industrial designers.
<br><br>
